%% PROPOSED: Cross-Team Autonomy Behavior Handoff Sequence
sequenceDiagram
    participant AUTO as Autonomy Lead
    participant AERO as Aero Lead
    participant SW as SW Lead
    participant HW as HW Lead
    participant FO as Field Operator
    participant PE as Project Engineer

    AUTO->>AERO: Share behavior requirements and mission envelope
    AERO-->>AUTO: Return aero constraints and performance targets
    AUTO->>SW: Request software interfaces and safety hooks
    AUTO->>HW: Request compute, sensor, and integration support
    SW-->>AUTO: Confirm SITL and HITL software readiness
    HW-->>AUTO: Confirm hardware availability and interface readiness
    AUTO->>FO: Deliver validation objectives and test package
    FO->>PE: Request test window, aircraft, and field approval
    PE-->>FO: Authorize test entry criteria and priorities
    FO-->>AUTO: Return HITL and flight observations with logs
    AUTO->>AERO: Review measured performance versus assumptions
    AUTO->>PE: Submit certification and release recommendation
    PE-->>AUTO: Approve release or require rework
